<br>
Tracking: This has been shelved due to technical issues. Unlike EQ, the DAoC client doesn’t track other players or creatures outside of a small radius. Implementing tracking would cause a severe server load increase.<br>
<br>
Guild Banks: This has turned out to be more difficult than expected. Tests on an early system were unsatisfactory, with such problems as items disappearing. Work on this continues.<br>
<br>
Housing: This is being worked on and they are committed to doing it right.<br>
<br>
True animal shapechanging: This has turned out to be more difficult than expected. This is on the back- burner currently.<br>
<br>
Spellcrafting: this is a top priority as the absence of spellcrafting leaves a big hole in the economy. This will happen.<br>
<br>
Disguise skill for assassins: This has turned out to be more difficult than expected. The issues include how to translate armour from one realm type to a different realm type and re-flagging the name over the head of the assassin when viewed by people of a different realm (including the realm the disguise is based on). If this happens, it won’t be soon.<br>
<br>
Traps for assassins: The preliminary traps are in as RA and are being tested live as it is not practical to thoroughly test traps on Pendragon.<br>
